text:
@EdibleHazmat @Craaazy1231 I think its just preliminary reaction and might retrace tomorrow’s trading day

If you look at the foundries/packagers: TSEM, CRDO, MRVL is up AH from the photonics/Ai demand confirmation

Maybe its due to AMD too since it went up 12%

A Kanata-based photonics semiconductor company, InPho is revolutionizing high-speed optical data connections used in cloud computing, AI infrastructure, data centres, and telecommunications.
 
We had a productive conversation with CEO Joe Costello on InPho's role across Ontario's supply chain and how their work can encourage new industry partnerships that will build on the $40B+ in tech investments Ontario has attracted since 2018.

@investontario

